               <p>RICHARD BARTRAM. I live in <placeName id="t18280911-378-crimeloc1962">Union-place, Battlebridge</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18280911-378-crimeloc1962" type="placeName" value="Union-place, Battlebridge"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18280911-378-crimeloc1962" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18280911-378-off1960 t18280911-378-crimeloc1962"></join>, and am a <rs id="t18280911-378-viclabel1963" type="occupation">carpet-beater</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18280911-378-victim2043 t18280911-378-viclabel1963"></join>. On the 31st of July I locked up my place, and left these three carpets and other things safe; between four and five o'clock next morning, I found the place broken open, and the things gone.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18280911-378-person2044">
                  ANDREW 
                  MITCHELL
               <interp inst="t18280911-378-person2044" type="surname" value="MITCHELL"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280911-378-person2044" type="given" value="ANDREW"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280911-378-person2044" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I open Copenhagen-gate. On the 1st of August I went out mushrooming, at a quarter-past three o'clock in the morning; at the bottom of the first field from Maiden-lane I heard three voices; I went down to the side of a bank - three men came up; I heard one say,"Here is a good place to hide them:" they hid one there. then went and hid the others about fifty yards off - I went and told the watchman; I do not know the men.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18280911-378-person2045">
                  RICHARD 
                  DEACON
               <interp inst="t18280911-378-person2045" type="surname" value="DEACON"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280911-378-person2045" type="given" value="RICHARD"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280911-378-person2045" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I superintend the watch. Mitchell came to me; I went with him, and found a large carpet under a elm tree, with some shrubs over it, and about fifty yards further found these hearth-rugs concealed; I left a man there to watch them, as I was called away - he left them, and they were taken away.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18280911-378-person2046">
                  WILLIAM 
                  BALDWIN
               <interp inst="t18280911-378-person2046" type="surname" value="BALDWIN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280911-378-person2046" type="given" value="WILLIAM"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280911-378-person2046" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a watchman. On Friday morning, about eleven o'clock, I saw the prisoner with a bag on his shoulder, and took him; I found two hearthrugs in the bag - I asked where he got them; he said,"Find it out."</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18280911-378-person2047">
                  ROBERT 
                  TEASDALE
               <interp inst="t18280911-378-person2047" type="surname" value="TEASDALE"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280911-378-person2047" type="given" value="ROBERT"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280911-378-person2047" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I took him into custody - he told me he had found them.(Property produced and sworn to.)</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. I was going over Kentish-townbridge; a young man employed me to carry the bag to the turnpike-house - he said he would overtake me, but he did not.</p>
               <p>The prisoner received a good character.</p>
               <p>
                  <rs id="t18280911-378-verdict1964" type="verdictDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18280911-378-verdict1964" type="verdictCategory" value="guilty"></interp>
               GUILTY
            </rs>. Aged 18.</p>
